				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Well I have finally done it...<a name="73218"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 14 05 3:52 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>After MANY years of enjoying EQ I have closed my account. This is not one of those tearful good bye posts that are so irksome. Instead I would like to share a few thoughts.
<br />

<br />
I only have time in my life for ONE game.
<br />

<br />
I left EQ because after 5 years or so everything just seemed more of the same.
<br />

<br />
I chose WoW because it seems like the best MMORPG game out currently (Until Vanguard comes out). And because it is NOT an SOE game.
<br />

<br />
I miss EQ greatly, any game I play now will be compared to it. And it is unlikely any will be better than it.
<br />

<br />
WoW is a visually pleasing , infact the world looks stunning.
<br />

<br />
WoW's game play is not NEARLY as intense as EQ is. EQ was built so that everyone in a group has a job to do and if one messes up (like a healer or a mezzer) then the whole group dies. In WoW there is only a slight preassure to group (from what I have seen so far) and the group make up does not really seem to matter much. Several casters can group and do just fine (try that in BOT).
<br />

<br />
Eventhough I am enjoying WoW I get the feeling I will tire of it fairly quickly.
<br />

<br />
No bard type class.. bummer.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Anyway that is my 2cp.
<br />
</span></td>
