				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">I'm not sure I'd say most.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Ok, half then. I play EQ because I like the mechanics of the particular game. I like playing baseball too because I like the mechanics of that game. If I could magically force myself to be 15 feet tall and hit a ball 900 feet the game wouldnt be as fun. If I could make it so I would never miss a swing at a ball, it would really take the fun outof it. If I could force the standards between bases to be 20 feet shorter so I could hit more inside-the-park-homeruns, that wouldnt be legit. I think pitchers throw the ball too fast. Lets put a cap on that too, or maybe a limit on foul-balls before a player has to give up. 
<br />

<br />
We accept the rules and parameters we're given, whether we like them or not, because that is what MAKES the game. Nobody is forcing us to play EQ. It's their game, they made it, they made the rules, they made the laws of the world in which we play in. We have no right to complain about the laws of their universe. The game has been in existance too long to start changing fundamental aspects. I firmly believe they would be hurting the game more than helping it by removing some of the 'annoyances'. 
<br />

<br />
X
