<br />
All I can say is that I tried WoW and for the reasons I've given earlier, I prefer it to EQ.  I can recall thinking about EQ, &quot;man this is lame, but it's what you have to do to have more fun later.&quot;  For example, if you're playing a caster, if you're smart, you'll end up standing in one place for maybe twenty minutes, chain casting one of each spell skill type, everytime you level to keep your casting skills up so that you don't fizzle spells so much.  Does this take skill?  No.  Is it fun?  No.  Is it just stupid?  Yes.   Same thing goes for a monk -- is it fun to have to run to the bank all the time to unload loot and coin so that you stay under the weight penalty? No.  Does it take skill?  No.  And there are a lot of things like that in EQ... stuff that's there seemingly just to slow you down.
<br />

<br />
So, vote with my feet I did.</span></td>
